FBIS4-63024 "drsov097_b_94047" FBIS-SOV-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Servicemen Arrested for Starting Fire at Arms Depot Servicemen Arrested for Starting Fire at Arms Depot LD1805172694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1552 GMT 18 May 94 LD1805172694 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Two servicemen who stood guard on the weapon depot of the Russian Pacific Fleet air force have been arrested on suspicion of causing a fire there on May 14. A spokesman for the Russian Prosecutor General's Office told Interfax that the men had been found to enter the store and try to extract certain parts from a missile. As they were doing this, there was a short circuit and the missile caught fire. They could not extinguish the fire which spread over the depot. The military prosecutor's office is investigating the case under the Prosecutor General's Office supervision.
